//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_depot_levy}

NOTE: This operation creates an
{rbtgi_depot}
- a cohesive unit of Recipe Bottle infrastructure including the depot project, build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool
that share their productive lifecycle.

The
{rbtr_payor}
creates a new depot infrastructure from the
{rbtgi_payor_project}.
The operation accepts no CLI parameters; depot identity is read from the kindled regime as `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_payor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_payor_authenticate}

//axhos_step
. *Validate region against Artifact Registry locations*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations/list[locations.list] for the authenticated project
.. {rbbc_require}
`{rbrr_gcp_region}` present in the returned location set

//axhos_step
. *Derive Depot Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«WORKER_POOL_STEM»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-pool` (resolved by `RBDC_GCB_POOL_STEM`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_BUCKET»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}b-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_GCS_BUCKET`)
.. NOTE: Joint length `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}` + `d-` + `${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` ≤ 30 chars (GCP project ID limit) is enforced upstream by `zrbrr_enforce` at regime kindle time, so this step performs no length validation.

//axhos_step
. *Create Depot Project*:
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/create[projects.create] with:
... projectId: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... displayName: `RB Depot: «RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... parent: `{rbrp_parent_type}s/{rbrp_parent_id}` (if parent_type != `none`)
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation
.. {rbbc_require}
project creation successful
.. NOTE: Project name collision against the GCP soft-delete graveyard surfaces here as fatal — re-using a moniker after `{rbtgo_depot_unmake}` requires waiting out the 30-day retention window. The operator-visible "fails if exists" property is intentional under the (CLOUD_PREFIX, MONIKER) shape.

//axhos_step
. *Link Billing Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/billing/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects/updateBillingInfo[cloudbilling.projects.updateBillingInfo] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. Set billingAccountName: `billingAccounts/{rbrp_billing_account_id}`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming billing linkage

//axhos_step
. *Get Depot Project Number*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.name` field (CRM v3 returns `projects/{number}`)
.. {rbbc_require}
valid numeric project number after extracting from name

//axhos_step
. *Enable Depot Project APIs*:
.. For each service in [`artifactregistry`, `cloudbuild`, `containeranalysis`, `iam`, `serviceusage`, `storage`]:
... Execute
{rbtoe_api_enable}
with service name and `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_require}
all APIs enabled successfully

//axhos_step
. *Create Private Worker Pool*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.workerPools/create[workerPools.create] with:
... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... workerPoolId: `«WORKER_POOL_STEM»`
... body:
+
----
{
  "privatePoolV1Config": {
    "workerConfig": {
      "machineType": "«RBRR_GCB_MACHINE_TYPE»"
    }
  }
}
----
.. NOTE:
{rbrr_gcb_machine_type}
is a Compute Engine machine type (e.g., `e2-standard-2`), consumed at pool creation time.
Pool scales to zero workers when idle — no idle cost accrues.
.. Treat HTTP 409 CONFLICT as success (pool already exists — idempotent)

//axhos_step
. *Verify IAM Propagation*:
.. NOTE: After API enablement, IAM permissions may not be immediately available due to eventual consistency.
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/list[artifactregistry.repositories.list] for `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` in `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.. Poll at `RBGC_EVENTUAL_CONSISTENCY_SEC` intervals until HTTP 200 or `RBGC_MAX_CONSISTENCY_SEC` timeout
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response confirming IAM propagation complete
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if timeout: "IAM propagation timeout - artifactregistry API not accessible"

//axhos_step
. *Create Build Bucket*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/storage/docs/json_api/v1/buckets/insert[storage.buckets.insert] with:
... name: `«BUILD_BUCKET»`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... lifecycle rule: delete objects after 1 day

//axhos_step
. *Create Container Repository*:
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/create[artifactregistry.repositories.create] with:
... repositoryId: `«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... format: `DOCKER`
... location: `{rbrr_gcp_region}`
... parent: `projects/«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»/locations/{rbrr_gcp_region}`
.. {rbbc_await}
returned operation

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_mason}
Service Account*:
.. NOTE: The
{rbtr_mason}
replaces Cloud Build's implicit service account to provide deterministic permissions and predictable authorization within the depot infrastructure.
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `mason-«RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... displayName: `Mason for RB Depot: «RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER»`
... project: `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«MASON_EMAIL»` from response `.email` field

//axhos_step
. *Configure
{rbtr_mason}
Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_repo} on `«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_bucket} on `«BUILD_BUCKET»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/storage.objectViewer`
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} on `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/viewer`
... Add `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/logging.logWriter`

//axhos_step
. *Enable Cloud Build service agent to impersonate
{rbtr_mason}*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_sa} on `«MASON_EMAIL»`
.. Add member: `serviceAccount:service-«PROJECT_NUMBER»@gcp-sa-cloudbuild.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
.. Grant role: `roles/iam.serviceAccountTokenCreator`
.. NOTE: Cloud Build service agent is Google-provisioned (auto-created when Cloud Build API is enabled), not a user-created service account. The `tokenCreator` role enables build steps running as {rbtr_mason} (via the build JSON's `serviceAccount` field) to generate fresh access tokens for GCP API calls — required for GAR authentication (docker login, crane push). This is distinct from `serviceAccountUser` (actAs), which the {rbtr_director} holds on {rbtr_mason} for submitting builds.
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM binding successful

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Confirm Depot Creation*:
.. {rbbc_show}
single-line success banner naming `«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` and the
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}
follow-up hint

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_depot}
. *Update Depot Tracking*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_depot_list_update}
to refresh per-moniker depot fact files

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates depot infrastructure with configured build bucket, container repository, Mason service account, and private worker pool — all derived from `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_governor_mantle}
to create the
{rbtr_governor}
for this depot.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_vouch}

NOTE: This operation vouches for every *pending*
{rbtga_ark}
in
{rbtgi_repository},
where *pending* means a hallmark whose subtree contains both
{rbtga_ark_image}
and
{rbtga_ark_about}
basenames but no
{rbtga_ark_vouch}.
The
{rbtr_director}
enumerates the full hallmark corpus via a single GAR REST `packages.list` call (the same shared helper used by
{rbtgo_hallmark_tally}),
identifies pending hallmarks, resolves the vessel name from each hallmark's
{rbtga_ark_about}
metadata (since vessel identity no longer lives in the GAR path), and dispatches
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
per hallmark.
Mode-awareness (conjure, bind, graft) lives inside
{rbtgo_ark_vouch};
batch vouch does not branch on mode.

NOTE: *Fail-fast semantics.* If
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
fails for any hallmark, the batch terminates via fatal error at that hallmark.
There is no skip-with-warning path and no summary-count-masking of failures: a broken hallmark demands immediate attention, not quiet continuation.

The
{rbtr_director}
batch-vouches arks:

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Enumerate Hallmark Packages*:
.. {rbbc_call}
the shared hallmark enumeration helper — a single
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[GAR REST API: packages.list]
call under `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/` (`RBGL_HALLMARKS_ROOT`), filtered to `<hallmark>/<basename>` shape
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PAIRS»` as sorted `<hallmark> <basename>` pairs (same shape produced for
{rbtgo_hallmark_tally})

//axhos_step
. *Identify Pending Hallmarks (Pass 1)*:
.. Iterate `«PAIRS»` in sort order; each contiguous run of the same hallmark is one
{rbtga_hallmark}'s
ark inventory.
.. For each hallmark, record whether
{rbtga_ark_image},
{rbtga_ark_about},
and
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
each appear in its run.
.. A hallmark is *pending* when `image` and `about` are present and `vouch` is absent.
Collect pending hallmarks into `«PENDING»` (in-memory sequence).
.. If `«PENDING»` is empty, the procedure completes successfully with no vouches submitted.

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Vessel and Vouch Per Pending Hallmark (Pass 2)*:
.. For each `«HALLMARK»` in `«PENDING»`:
... Extract the hallmark's
{rbtga_ark_about}
artifact (package `«HALLMARKS_ROOT»/«HALLMARK»/about`, tag `«HALLMARK»`) to a scratch directory via the shared GAR artifact extraction helper
... Read `.vessel_name` from the extracted `build_info.json` via `jq`
... {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_DIR»` as `«RBRR_VESSEL_DIR»/«VESSEL_NAME»`
... {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_DIR»` exists on disk — the vessel named in `about` metadata must correspond to a configured vessel in the current regime
... {rbbc_fatal}
if the `about` artifact cannot be extracted, `build_info.json` is missing, `.vessel_name` is empty, or `«VESSEL_DIR»` does not exist — the `about` artifact is the sole source of vessel identity for this batch; a gap there is a fail-fast stop
... Invoke
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
with `«VESSEL_DIR»` and `«HALLMARK»`.
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
loads the vessel's
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
internally and dispatches the appropriate verification (conjure: SLSA DSSE verification; bind: digest-pin; graft: GRAFTED stamp).
... {rbbc_fatal}
if
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
fails — the batch terminates at the broken hallmark.

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
. *Display Summary*:
.. {rbbc_show}
`Batch vouch complete — N/N hallmark(s) vouched` where N is the initial pending count

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution creates one
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
artifact per pending hallmark (N total, where N = initial pending count).
The batch runs sequentially; a failure at any hallmark halts the remainder.
+
*Scope of vessel resolution*: Reading `vessel_name` from `build_info.json` is a narrow anticipation of the broader vessel-from-metadata pattern (AAL territory) — applied locally inside batch vouch only, because
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
's signature still takes a vessel directory.
Other operations (tally, plumb, abjure) continue to not surface vessel.
+
*Two-pass shape*: Pass 1 collects pending hallmarks into memory before Pass 2 begins processing.
Each
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
invocation sources credentials and issues Cloud Build calls that would silently consume loop stdin if the pending set were streamed; the in-memory collection decouples enumeration from dispatch.
+
*Idempotency*: Re-running batch vouch after a successful batch finds an empty pending set (every prior pending hallmark now has `vouch` present) and exits with no action.
+
*No mode pre-check*: Earlier shapes of this operation pre-probed SLSA provenance for conjure-mode hallmarks to skip-with-warning those lacking provenance.
That pattern is gone — all mode-specific verification happens inside
{rbtgo_ark_vouch},
and any failure there surfaces as a fail-fast stop rather than being absorbed into a summary count.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_invest}

NOTE: This operation invests a {rbtr_director} {giam_service_account} into the {rbtgi_depot_project}.
The {rbtr_governor} mints the SA, generates its credential key, and writes the RBRA bytes to the assay output slot.
The operation is singleton-per-role: no instance argument; the SA identity is derived from regime constants as `${RBCC_role_director}-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}`.
Fatal if the SA already exists — operator must {rbtgo_director_divest} first to re-key.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Derive
{rbtr_director}
Service Account Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»` as `${RBCC_role_director}-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (singleton per role per depot, regime-kindled via
{rbrr_depot_moniker})
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` as `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»@${RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID}.iam.gserviceaccount.com` (depot project ID derived from `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)`)

//axhos_step
. *Preflight: Confirm Service Account Does Not Exist*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if HTTP 200: service account already exists — operator must execute
{rbtgo_director_divest}
before re-investing this role
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 404 to proceed

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_director}
Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»`
... displayName: `Recipe Bottle Director`
... description: `Create/destroy container images for depot ${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}`
... project:
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_UNIQUE_ID»` from response `.uniqueId` field

//axhos_step
. *Verify Service Account Propagation*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_poll}
with backoff until HTTP 200 (newly-created SA may not be immediately resolvable by email)
.. NOTE: Poll must use the email address, not the numeric ID. The email-based lookup path has independent propagation from the UID-based path, and subsequent steps (keys.list, keys.create) all use the email address. Polling by UID can succeed while the email path still returns 404.
.. {rbbc_require}
service account accessible by email

//axhos_step
. *Preflight: Ensure Pristine Key State*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/list[serviceAccounts.keys.list] for `«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_store}
`«EXISTING_KEYS»` from response `.keys[]`
.. {rbbc_require}
no keys with `keyType: USER_MANAGED` exist
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if USER_MANAGED keys found: "Manual cleanup required via Console"

//axhos_step
. *Generate Service Account Key*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts.keys/create[serviceAccounts.keys.create] for `«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with:
... privateKeyType: `TYPE_GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_FILE`
.. Retry up to `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_MAX` times on HTTP 404 with `RBGC_SA_KEY_CREATE_RETRY_DELAY_SEC` delay between attempts
.. NOTE: SA read operations (GET by email, keys.list) may succeed while keys.create POST returns 404 "does not exist" due to write-path propagation delay. Google link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/service-accounts-create[documents]: "you might need to wait 60 seconds or more before you use the service account." The 404 confirms no key was created, making retry safe. See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` from response `.privateKeyData` field
.. {rbtoe_rbra_generate}
converts `«DIRECTOR_PRIVATE_KEY_DATA»` to `«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»`

//axhos_step
. *Get Depot Project Number*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/resource-manager/reference/rest/v3/projects/get[projects.get] for
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«PROJECT_NUMBER»` from `.projectNumber` field

//axhos_step
. *Grant Project-Level Permissions*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_project} for
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
... `roles/cloudbuild.builds.editor` (submit and manage builds)
... `roles/viewer` (read project resources)
... `roles/cloudbuild.workerPoolUser` (use private pool for vouch `builds.create`)
.. Policy version: 3
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM policy update successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtr_mason}
Impersonation*:
.. NOTE:
{rbtr_director}
submits builds that execute as
{rbtr_mason}.
This requires `serviceAccountUser` permission on
{rbtr_mason}.
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_sa} on
{rbtr_mason}
service account
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/iam.serviceAccountUser`
.. {rbbc_require}
IAM binding successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_build_bucket}
Access*:
.. {rbtoe_iam_grant_bucket} on
{rbtgi_build_bucket}
.. Add `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with roles:
... `roles/storage.objectCreator` (upload sources)
... `roles/storage.objectViewer` (verify uploads)
.. {rbbc_require}
bucket IAM update successful

//axhos_step
. *Grant
{rbtgi_repository}
Admin Access*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/getIamPolicy[repositories.getIamPolicy] via HTTP GET with `options.requestedPolicyVersion=3` query parameter
.. NOTE: {gar_registry} proto specifies GET for `getIamPolicy` with no `additional_bindings` for POST. Using POST fails intermittently with HTTP 404 (transcoding layer rejection, not missing repository). See <<rbscig_iam_grant_contracts>>.
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 — 404 means repository does not exist (real error, not empty policy)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories/setIamPolicy[repositories.setIamPolicy] for
{rbtgi_repository}
.. *Complete policy write*: Add ALL expected bindings to the read policy, regardless of what the read returned:
... `serviceAccount:«DIRECTOR_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.repoAdmin` — Director manages images
... `serviceAccount:«MASON_EMAIL»` with `roles/artifactregistry.writer` — Mason pushes images at build time
.. NOTE: Same complete-policy-write pattern as the secret IAM step. Prevents stale read from overwriting Mason's writer binding set by {rbtgo_depot_levy}.
.. {rbbc_require}
repository IAM set with all expected bindings

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtgi_rbra_file}
. *Deliver Credential to Assay Output Slot*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_RBRA_FILE»` RBRA bytes to the assay output slot via the producer-output discipline (the orphan's `${BURD_OUTPUT_DIR}` credential write retires)

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution invests director service account `«DIRECTOR_ACCOUNT_NAME»` with build management permissions, generates its credential key, and writes the RBRA file to the assay output slot.

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_retriever_invest}

NOTE: This operation invests a {rbtr_retriever} {giam_service_account} into the {rbtgi_depot_project} with read-only {rbtgi_repository} access.
The {rbtr_governor} mints the SA, generates its credential key, and writes the RBRA bytes to the assay output slot.
The operation is singleton-per-role: no instance argument; the SA identity is derived from regime constants as `${RBCC_role_retriever}-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}`.
Fatal if the SA already exists — operator must {rbtgo_retriever_divest} first to re-key.

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_governor}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_governor_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GOVERNOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Derive
{rbtr_retriever}
Service Account Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»` as `${RBCC_role_retriever}-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (regime-kindled from
{rbrr_depot_moniker})
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»` as `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»@${RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID}.iam.gserviceaccount.com`
.. NOTE: `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID` is derived from `(RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX, RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER)` at regime kindle time; no operator-supplied project ID field is referenced.

//axhos_step
. *Probe for Pre-existing Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if HTTP 200: service account already exists — operator must run
{rbtgo_retriever_divest}
before re-investing
.. Continue only on HTTP 404 (account absent — proceed to create)

//axhos_step
. *Create
{rbtr_retriever}
Service Account*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/create[iam.serviceAccounts.create] with:
... accountId: `«RETRIEVER_ACCOUNT_NAME»`
... displayName: `Recipe Bottle Retriever`
... description: `Read-only access to Google Artifact Registry for depot ${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}`
... project:
{rbtgi_depot_project}
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RETRIEVER_UNIQUE_ID»` from response `.uniqueId` field

//axhos_step
. *Verify Service Account Propagation*:
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/iam/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.serviceAccounts/get[iam.serviceAccounts.get] for `projects/-/serviceAccounts/«RETRIEVER_EMAIL»`
.. {rbbc_poll}
with backoff until HTTP 200 (newly-created SA may not be immediately resolvable by email)
.. NOTE: Poll must use the email address, not the numeric ID. The email-based lookup path has independent propagation from the UID-based path, and subsequent steps (keys.list, keys.create) all use the email address. Polling by UID can succeed while the email path still returns 404.
.. {rbbc_require}
service account accessible by email

//axhos_step
. *Preflight: Ensure Pristine Key State*:
.. {rbbc_call}
